terminologies.name: Subrogation
terminologies.definition: Subrogation is the process that allows your insurer to recoup costs from the at-fault drivers insurance company for expenses paid after an accident. Subrogation makes it possible for drivers to receive insurance claims payouts before the insurance companies agree on who was at fault. The at-fault drivers insurance will ultimately cover the cost.
